    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1952-03-24T12:34:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1952-03-24T12:34:00-05:00" n="1470"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1470">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">641.86A/3–1152: Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 1470<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Embassy in Saudi Arabia</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d1470fn1">Repeated as telegram 4692 to London and 593 to
                        Baghdad. Drafted by <persName corresp="#p_AFH1">Awalt</persName> and cleared
                        by <gloss target="#t_EUR1">EUR</gloss>, <gloss target="#t_BNA1">BNA</gloss>,
                        and <gloss target="#t_NEA1">NEA</gloss>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1952-03-24T12:34:00-05:00"
                            >March 24, 1952—12:34 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>351. You may inform <persName corresp="#p_IAAF1">Feisal</persName> US is moved by
                    earnestness of his and <gloss target="#t_HM1">HM</gloss>’s attitude this problem
                        (<gloss target="#t_Embtel1">Embtel</gloss>s 474 and 477, Mar 10 and 11<note
                        n="2" xml:id="d1470fn2">
                        <ref target="#d1467">Documents 1467</ref> and <ref target="#d1468"
                            >1468</ref>.</note>) and intends making serious approach to UK (<gloss
                        target="#t_Deptel1">Deptel</gloss> 4691 to London Mar 24, rptd Jidda
                        350<note n="3" xml:id="d1470fn3">
                        <ref target="#d1469">
                            <hi rend="italic">Supra</hi>
                        </ref>.</note>). Approach made out of sincere concern for relations between
                    our two good friends despite delicacy always attendant when outsider becomes
                    involved family quarrel. Must similarly enjoin <gloss target="#t_SAG1"
                        >SAG</gloss>, however, to meet any Brit approach halfway. Compromise cannot
                    be one-sided. Inflexible view . . . re . . . rights to land and people not
                    conducive success . . . . This alone cld block progress.<note n="4"
                        xml:id="d1470fn4">Telegram 551 from Jidda, Apr. 8, reported the message in
                        this telegram had been delivered to <persName corresp="#p_IAAF1"
                            >Faisal</persName> the previous evening. (641.86A/4–852)</note>
                </p>
                <p>You might also assure <persName corresp="#p_IAAF1">Feisal</persName> we know of
                    no Brit plan unite Iraq, Kuwait (<gloss target="#t_Embtel1">Embtel</gloss> 474),
                    and feel sure there is none. If this suggested to <gloss target="#t_SAG1"
                        >SAG</gloss> by recent visit Sheikh Kuwait to Iraq you might add we know
                    this visit caught Brit by surprise and was initiated by <gloss target="#t_IG1"
                        >IG</gloss>. Wld also appear illegal for Brit support absorption Kuwait by
                    Iraq and lose preferential position UK enjoys in Kuwait. Dept notes <gloss
                        target="#t_SA3">SA</gloss> tendency be over-suspicious Brit which is
                    destructive mutual confidence so necessary for conducting negots under best
                    auspices.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_AD1">
                            <hi rend="strong">
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                            </hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
